CEUR Workshop Proceedings (CEUR-WS.org) is a free open-access publication service of Sun SITE Central Europe operated under the umbrella of RWTH Aachen University. CEUR-WS.org is a recognized ISSN publication series, ISSN 1613-0073. CEUR-WS.org is hosted at http://SunSITE.Informatik.RWTH-Aachen.DE/Publications/CEUR-WS/. The publisher of the CEUR-WS.org site excluding the proceedings volumes is Ruzica Piskac. The publishers of the proceedings volumes (CEUR-WS.org/Vol-1, CEUR-WS.org/Vol-2, etc.) are the respective editors of the volumes. This service is provided by the CEUR-WS.org Team. See end of the page for contact details and Impressum.

CEUR Workshop Proceedings (CEUR-WS.org)

Online Proceedings for Scientific Workshops

Unless stated explicitely and in conformance to the legal Disclaimer of Sun SITE Central Europe (CEUR) and the legal Disclaimer of Technical University of Aachen (RWTH), the copyright for the workshop proceedings as a compilation, i.e. CEUR-WS.org/Vol-1, CEUR-WS.org/Vol-2 etc., is with the respective proceedings editors. The copyright for the individual items (subsuming any type of computer-represented files containing articles, software demos, videos, etc.) within a proceedings volume is owned by default by their respective authors. Copying of items, in particular papers, and proceedings volumes is permitted only for private and academic purposes. The permission for academic use implies an attribution obligation, i.e., you must properly cite the items that you use in your own published work. Modification of items is not permitted unless a suitable license is granted by its copyright owners. Copying or use for commercial purposes is forbidden unless an explicit permission is acquired from the copyright owners. Re-publication of a CEUR Workshop Proceedings volume or of an individual item inside a proceedings volume requires permission by the copyright owners, i.e. either the respective proceedings editors, or the authors of the respective item in that volume, or both. Mirroring of the CEUR-WS.org web site, or parts of it, is prohibited. The label 'CEUR Workshop Proceedings' and the CEUR-WS logo are owned by the publisher of this site.

Important changes are reported in our timeline. CEUR-WS.org provides its services free of charge to the academic community. We are grateful for small donations in case you want to express your appreciation of our service. We are also grateful for donations of scripts that ease our tasks, for example scripts that excerpt the bibliographic data out of index files.

Proceedings editors: Follow instructions on how to submit your proceedings volume.

Miscellaneous

Workshop organizers can look here for information on how to submit electronic workshop proceedings to CEUR. The procedure takes few minutes. It requires the ability to upload files to a FTP server and a fax where you acknowledge the nature of CEUR Workshop Proceedings as a free service for academia and science.

Some statistics about CEUR-WS.org. In January 2011, CEUR-WS.org published about 10.500 papers distributed over roughly 680 workshop proceedings. There are a few thousand real paper downloads (downloads by search engines and from the proceedings FTP archive not counted) per day from CEUR-WS.org. Between 1995 and 2002, CEUR-WS.org was offline for less than 10 days in total. The offline times were mostly due to network re-configurations at RWTH Aachen. Since its start in 1995, the number of volumes published per year has shown solid growth.

In the list above, the bibliographic identifier of a publication is the 'ONLINE' token. It points to the directory containing all material of the publication. Most papers are currently in PDF or PostScript formats. Papers in Adobe's PDF format can be viewed by the free-of-charge Adobe Reader and by completely free alternatives such as Evince. Note that not all PostScript viewers are able to display complicated PostScript documents. We had no problems with Ghostscript on Macintosh, Unix/Linux, and Windows. Please upgrade for these tools to recent versions if some paper does not display correctly. Any browser supporting HTML4 may be used to view the HTML pages. Even 'lynx' should work. Some graphics are in PNG (portable network graphics) format, which is not supported by older editions of some browsers, however.

As a supplement to the ONLINE access, there is an ARCHIVE link pointing to a compressed version of the publication, i.e. all papers plus the index file, that can be downloaded as a single 'zip' archive file. Such a file can be unpacked by Unix 'unzip' command as well as by popular utilities like WinZIP and StuffIt Expander w/ Enhancer. Using the archive is much faster than downloading the individual papers. You can access it via anonymous ftp from

  • ftp://SunSITE.Informatik.RWTH-Aachen.DE/pub/publications/CEUR-WS.

The FTP archive also contains the MD5 checksums of the volumes. See file README.html for instructions. A subset of CEUR-WS proceedings volumes is indexed by DBLP. Proceedings editors need to contact services such as DBLP themselves, if they want their volume to be indexed. Popular search engines including some specializing in scientific publications are scanning CEUR-WS.org on a regular basis as well. We have no formal relation with any of them!
